message: "I'm proud of the work we do to protect and serve the victims of this heinous crime. By using our resources and working together, we're able to approach this issue from many perspectives," said Attorney General Mike DeWine.

data.description: A new report from the Ohio Attorney General's Office details the number of victims, traffickers and consumers in the state.
data.title: 208 Suspected Human Trafficking Victims In Ohio In 2017
